HEADWORD: Statuesque
<hw>Stat`u*esque"</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧ch`⟦oomac⟧*⟦ecr⟧sk" <it>or</it>
st⟦acr⟧t`⟦usl⟧*⟦ecr⟧sk")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Partaking of, or
exemplifying, the characteristics of a statue; having the symmetry, or
other excellence, of a statue artistically made; <as>as,
<ex>statuesque</ex>limbs; a <ex>statuesque</ex> attitude</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their characters are mostly <qex>statuesque</qex> even in this
respect, that they have no background.</q> <rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

